<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773774>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 14. Stereo images of MNHN HGP 46, left upper male canine of Listriodon splendens from Bonnefont, France, first published by Crouzel (1980) as Sus (?) doati. a: ventral view, b: radicular section, c: dorsal view, d: oblique lateral view, e: oblique medial view." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773774/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773755>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 6. Stereo supero-anterior views of the skull of Listriodon splendens from Nebisuyu, Turkey (EUNHM PV 3075). Arrows show the two grooves associated with the supraorbital foramina (scales are 10 mm for the anterior part of the frontal bones, and 5 cm for the parietals)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773755/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773764>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 10. Stereoscopic views of EUNHM PV 3075, upper left male canine in maxilla fragment from Nebisuyu, Turkey, attributed to Listriodon splendens. Radicular end is to the right. Arrows indicate extent of wear facet caused by abrasion against the lower canine. a: antero-dorsal, b: oblique anterior view, c: ventral, d: dorsal views." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773764/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773778>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 16. Listriodon splendens from Helsighausen, Switzerland. a: PIMUZ A/V 1237, left I1/ (a1 – lingual, a2 – mesial, a3 – labial views); b: PIMUZ A/V 1236, right mandible containing p/3–m/3 (b1 – stereo occlusal view, b2 – buccal view)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773778/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4773772>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 13. Reconstruction of the upper canines of the Nebisuyu listriodont (EUNHM PV 3075). a: dorsal view (anterior towards top of page), b: anterior view. The twoheaded arrows show the orientation of the scratches on the wear facet caused during thegosis with the lower canine. These orientations are approximate." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4773772/files/figure.png" .

